1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Qc2 g6 5. Bf4 Bf5 6. Qb3 Qb6 7. e3 $1 {It is
better to postpone c4-c5 until the safety of the Bf4 is guaranteed by means of
h2-h3.} Na6 $5 {An interesting yet insufficient attempt for counterplay. By
the quick activation of the knight, Black hopes to disturb White's normal
development.} (7... Bxb1 8. Rxb1 e6 9. h3 $5 $14) (7... Nbd7 8. Nc3 e6 9. h3 $5
{[%cal Gc4c5] /\ c5+/=}) 8. Nc3 Nb4 $1 (8... Qxb3 9. axb3 Nb4 10. Ra4 $1) (8...
Bg7 $6 {is not possible anymore} 9. cxd5 $1 Nb4 (9... cxd5 10. Qxb6 $16) 10.
dxc6 $3 bxc6 (10... Nc2+ 11. Kd1 Qxb3 12. axb3 Nxa1 13. cxb7 $18) 11. Rc1 O-O (
11... Nc2+ 12. Kd2) 12. Bc4 Bd3 13. Ne5 $18 {and White won easily in Dlugy,M
-Ninov,D Blagoevgrad 2013}) 9. c5 $1 Nd3+ (9... Nc2+ $4 10. Qxc2 $18) (9... Bc2
$4 10. Qa3 $1 $18 {[%csl Rb4,Rb6]}) (9... Qa5 $6 10. Rc1 {[%cal Ga2a3] /\ a3+-}
Bc8 $8 (10... b6 11. Ne5 Rc8 12. a3 Na6 13. Nxc6 $1 Rxc6 14. Qb5 $18) 11. Be2
$16) 10. Bxd3 Qxb3 11. axb3 Bxd3 12. Ne5 {Black's domination on the light
squares is only temporary.} Bf5 (12... Ba6 $4 13. Nxc6 $18) (12... Bb5 13. Nxb5
cxb5 14. Ra5 a6 15. Ke2 {[%cal Gh1a1,Gc5c6] /\ Rha1, c6+-}) 13. b4 $1 {Black
lost precious time in obtaining the bishop pair and now White is successfully
undoubling the pawns.} Nd7 $1 (13... Ne4 14. b5 $1 Nxc3 15. bxc6 $1 bxc6 16.
bxc3 Bd7 17. Ra6 $18) (13... Nh5 14. b5 Nxf4 15. exf4 f6 16. bxc6 bxc6 (16...
fxe5 17. cxb7 Rb8 18. c6 $18) 17. Nxc6 $18) 14. b5 Nxe5 (14... Nb8 15. Na4 $18
{[%cal Ra4b6] ><b6}) (14... f6 15. bxc6 fxe5 16. cxb7 $1 Rb8 17. c6 $18) (14...
g5 15. bxc6 (15. Bxg5) (15. Bg3) 15... bxc6 16. Nxc6 gxf4 17. Nxd5) 15. Bxe5 f6
16. Bg3 $1 e5 $1 {This is always Black's only hope.} (16... Bd7 17. b4 $16) (
16... Bg7 17. b4 $16) 17. dxe5 $6 {In my opinion, there was no need to break
the pawn chain and to unleash Black's bishops.} (17. b4 $6 exd4 18. exd4 Bh6) (
17. bxc6 $1 bxc6 18. Ra6 Kd7 19. b4 Bd3 20. b5 cxb5 (20... Bxb5 21. Nxb5 cxb5
22. Kd2) 21. Nxd5 $16) 17... Bxc5 18. O-O $1 Kf7 (18... fxe5 $14) 19. Rfc1 Rhc8
(19... Be7 20. bxc6 bxc6 21. Ra6 $16 {[%csl Ra7,Rc6] ><a7, c6} Rhc8 22. Rca1
fxe5 23. Bxe5 Bd3 24. Rxa7 Rxa7 25. Rxa7 Ke6 26. Bg3 h5) (19... fxe5 $5 20.
Bxe5 Rhc8 $14) 20. exf6 $5 (20. bxc6) 20... Kxf6 $6 (20... Bb4 $14) 21. bxc6
bxc6 22. Ra6 $16 {After his small inaccuracy, White is coming back on top.} Ke7
$2 {The position was full of tricks, and Black eventually cracks.} (22... Ke6
23. Nxd5 $1 Kxd5 24. Ra5 $18) (22... Bd3 23. Nxd5+ Kf7 24. Ra5 cxd5 25. Raxc5
$18) (22... Kf7 $8 23. Na4 Bb4 24. Raxc6 Bd7 $1 25. Rc7 Ke8 $16) 23. Nxd5+ $1 {
Black should not have missed this.} (23. Nxd5+ cxd5 24. Rxc5 Rxc5 25. Bd6+ {
[%csl Ra7] ><a7}) (23. Na4 $2 Bb4 24. Raxc6 Rxc6 25. Rxc6 Bd7 26. Rc7 Rc8 $1
$10 {^^}) 1-0

