1. c4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. d4 Nf6 4. Qc2 g6 5. Bf4 Bf5 6. Qb3 Qb6 7. e3 Nbd7 8. Nc3
Qxb3 9. axb3 e6 10. h3 $1 (10. c5 Nh5 $1 {with counterplay.}) 10... h6 ({
It was worth trying} 10... Bb4 {but it is doubtful that it is any better:} 11.
Nd2 h5 12. f3 h4 13. Be2 (13. Na2 Be7) 13... Ke7 14. Kf2 $14) 11. c5 $1 {
The start of the typical plan. Black is going to get badly squeezed.} g5 12.
Bh2 a6 13. b4 Rc8 {The first wave has been stopped.} 14. Nd2 $1 {[%cal Gd2b3,
Gb3a5]} Be7 15. Nb3 Bd8 16. Na5 $1 Bxa5 17. bxa5 $1 {[%cal Ga1a4,Ga4b4] Now
the second wave is coming - Ra4-b4 is a nasty threat.} Kd8 (17... e5 {blocking
the bishop does not help, either.} 18. Ra4 $1 O-O 19. Rb4 Rfe8 20. Kd2 Rb8 21.
dxe5 Nxe5 22. Bxe5 Rxe5 23. Bxa6 Nd7 24. Rxb7 Ra8 25. b4 $3 Rxa6 26. g4 Be6 27.
f4 $18 {[%csl Re5] trapping the rook in the middle of the board.}) 18. Ra4 Ra8
19. Rb4 Kc8 {Black survived somehow, but only to realize that there is no hope
left.} 20. Be2 Ne8 21. Kd2 Nc7 22. Na4 Bg6 23. h4 $1 {The opening of the
second front is decisive.} f6 24. Bg3 (24. Bd6 Rh7 25. hxg5 hxg5 26. Rxh7 Bxh7
27. Bh5) 24... Rh7 25. f3 (25. hxg5 hxg5 26. Rxh7 Bxh7 27. Bh5 {was winning by
complete domination.}) 25... Nb5 26. Bd3 $6 {The first slight inaccuracy.} ({
The simplest was} 26. Nb6+ Nxb6 27. axb6 Kd7 28. Ra4 {[%csl Rb5,Rb7] The
knight on b5 is out of play and White's clearcut idea is to open the path to
the b7 pawn.} Rg8 29. Raa1 Rhh8 30. hxg5 hxg5 31. Rxh8 Rxh8 32. f4 $18) 26...
Bxd3 27. Kxd3 gxh4 (27... Kd8 28. hxg5 fxg5 29. Nb6 Nxb6 30. axb6 Ke7 31. Rh5
Rg8 32. Ra4 Kf7 33. Ra1 Kg6 34. Rah1 a5 35. f4 $18) 28. Rxh4 Kd8 29. Nb6 Nxb6
30. axb6 Ke7 31. Bf4 h5 32. Ra4 Rg8 33. g4 Rgh8 34. g5 Rg8 35. gxf6+ Kxf6 36.
Be5+ Kf7 37. Ra1 Rg2 38. Rah1 Rxb2 39. Rxh5 Rxh5 40. Rxh5 Kg6 41. Rh8 Rb3+ 42.
Kd2 Rb2+ 43. Ke1 a5 44. Ra8 $2 {After this move the fight starts all over
again.} ({The most clever finish would have been} 44. Rb8 $1 a4 45. Rxb7 a3 46.
Ra7 Nxa7 47. bxa7 a2 48. a8=Q Rb1+ 49. Kf2 a1=Q 50. Qg8+ Kh5 51. Qf7+ Kh4 52.
Bf6+ {with mate}) 44... Na3 45. Rxa5 Nc2+ {White won after some help of the
opponent on move 75.} 1-0

