10. h3 $1 {An important prophylactic move as Black was treatening Nh5.} e6 11.
Ra1 {[%cal Gb4b5] Threatening b5.} Rc8 12. Bd3 Be7 13. Nf3 {[%cal Gf3d2,Gd2b3,
Gb3a5] Starting the journey to the ideal square.} Bd8 14. O-O (14. Ke2 $1)
14... Nb8 (14... Bc7 $6 15. Bxc7 Rxc7 16. b5) 15. Nd2 Bc7 $1 {An important
defensive manouevre, safely blocking White's first wave.} 16. Nb3 Bxf4 17. exf4
g6 18. Na5 Rc7 {Even if Black manages to hold he is doomed to passivity. The
last hope is to create a fortress.} 19. Rae1 Kd8 20. g4 Re8 21. Re3 Nbd7 22.
Rfe1 Nf8 23. Kg2 Rce7 $2 {Missing the standard sacrifice. It is not a big joy
to defend for 100 more moves but in my opinion this should nearly be a
fortress for Black.} 24. Bxa6 $3 bxa6 25. Nxc6+ Kd7 26. Nxe7 Rb8 27. Rb3 Kxe7
28. Ra1 $18 *

