{White forgot to insert h3 and now Black could have exchanged the important
bishop on f4.} 11... Nh5 $2 {The idea to avoid the weakening move g5 is
refuted.} (11... g5 12. Bg3 Nh5 $11) 12. Be5 f6 $6 {It was better to admit the
mistake and to go back.} (12... Nf6 13. Rac1 Nxe5 14. Nxe5 Ne8 15. Rc2 $14) 13.
Bc7 $1 {Obviously, Black had missed this intermediate move.} (13. Bxg6 $6 fxe5
$36) 13... Qxc7 14. Bxg6 Nf4 15. exf4 Qxf4 16. Rad1 f5 (16... Qg4 17. Bb1 $16 {
The two bishops are not sufficient to compensate for the defects in the pawn
structure.}) 17. Bh5 $1 {[%csl Re6,Rf7,Rg6] Black has great problems with the
backward pawn on e6 and the light squares.} Qc7 ({The pawn is untouchable.} 
17... Nxd4 $2 18. Nxd4 Bxd4 19. Nxd5 $18) 18. Ne2 Bd7 19. g3 $1 Qd6 20. Nf4
Rac8 21. Rfe1 Na5 22. Qd3 Nc4 23. Re2 Qb6 24. Rde1 Nd6 25. Rxe6 $1 {Babula
showed great technique to convert his advantage and the finish is great.} Bxe6
26. Rxe6 Rfd8 27. Nxd5 Rc1+ 28. Kg2 Qxb2 29. Ne7+ Kh8 30. Qe3 Rc3 31. Rxh6+ 1-0

