1. Nf3 d5 2. d4 Nf6 3. c4 c6 4. Qb3 dxc4 5. Qxc4 Bg4 6. Nc3 Nbd7 7. e4 Bxf3 (
7... e5 $1) 8. gxf3 e5 9. Be3 Bd6 (9... exd4 $1) 10. O-O-O Qc7 11. dxe5 $1 $16
{After two inaccurate moves, Black is already nearly lost. White's pawn mass
supported by two strong bishops is quickly smashing Black's pieces.} Bxe5 ({
Equally bad would have been} 11... Nxe5 12. Qd4 $1 Rd8 13. f4 Neg4 14. e5 Be7
15. Qxa7 Rxd1+ 16. Nxd1 Nxe3 (16... Nd5 17. Bd2 O-O 18. Bh3) 17. Nxe3 $16) 12.
Ne2 $1 Nh5 {Fighting to prevent the pawn march by all means - but in vain.} 13.
Kb1 $1 $18 {and it is over!} Nb6 (13... O-O 14. f4 Bf6 15. e5 Be7 16. Ng3 $18)
(13... Rd8 14. Bh3 Nb6 15. Qc1 $18 (15. Qc5 $18)) 14. Qb4 $1 {Keeping the
Black king in the center.} (14. Qc1 Bd6 15. f4 g6 16. Ng3 Ng7 17. e5 Be7 18. f5
Nxf5 19. Nxf5 gxf5 20. Bh3 $18 {with a decisive attack against the uncastled
king.}) 14... Nf4 (14... Rd8 15. Bh3) 15. a4 $1 Nxe2 16. Bxe2 Bf6 (16... Nd7
17. f4 Bxf4 18. Bxf4 Qxf4 19. Rxd7 $18) 17. f4 Be7 18. Qd4 O-O 19. a5 Nc8 20.
e5 (20. Rhg1 g6 21. f5 $1 {is much stronger; but the move White played is good
enough.}) 20... Qxa5 21. f5 f6 22. Rhg1 fxe5 23. Qg4 Bf6 24. Rd7 1-0

