1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Qc2 dxc4 5. Qxc4 Bg4 6. Nc3 Nbd7 7. e4 Bxf3 8.
gxf3 e5 9. Be3 exd4 $1 10. Bxd4 Bd6 11. O-O-O Qe7 (11... Qc7 {is Black's most
precise continuation.}) 12. Ne2 $1 {[%cal Ge2g3,Gg3f5] The knight is heading
to reach f5.} Bc5 $1 {Exchanging the dark-squared bishops is Black's primary
task if he wants to stay safe.} 13. Ng3 $1 (13. Rg1) (13. Bh3) (13. Bc3 O-O-O
$1) 13... g6 (13... Bxd4 $1 {White keeps some pressure in the endgame, too,
but at least Black's king is safe.} 14. Rxd4 Qc5 15. Nf5 O-O 16. Rg1 g6 17. f4
$14) 14. Bc3 $1 {Preserving the bishop is the best way to continue the fight
as the pawn on f2 is not important at all.} Bxf2 (14... b5 15. Qe2 b4 (15...
Bb4 $2 16. Rxd7) 16. Bd2) (14... Ne5 15. Qe2 Bb4 16. Bxb4 Qxb4 17. f4 $14) 15.
Bh3 $1 {[%csl Re8] Black's king is arrested.} Nb6 (15... O-O 16. Bxd7 Nxd7 17.
Nf5) (15... O-O-O 16. e5) (15... Rf8 16. Bb4) 16. Qe2 Bc5 (16... Bxg3 17. hxg3)
17. b3 $6 {The idea is to have Ba1 in response to Bb4; but, as usual, the most
natural move is the best.} (17. Rhe1 $1 Bb4 (17... O-O 18. Qg2 Kh8 19. Nh5 gxh5
20. Qg5) (17... Na4 18. Bxf6 Qxf6 19. Bd7+ Kf8 20. Qc2) 18. Nf5 $3 Qc5 19. Nd6+
Kf8 20. Nxb7 Qe7 21. Bxb4 Qxb4 22. Qc2 Kg7 23. Nd6 $18) 17... O-O (17... Bb4
18. Ba1 O-O 19. Nf5) 18. Nf5 $2 ({The winning idea is the insidious manouevre} 
18. Qg2 $3 Kh8 19. Qd2 $3 {[%cal Gd2g5] and Qg5+-}) 18... gxf5 19. Bxf5 $2 (19.
Qg2+ Ng4 20. exf5 Qg5+ 21. Kb2 Nd5 22. Qxg4 Qxg4 23. fxg4 Rfe8 $15) 19... Bb4
$2 ({White's compensation after} 19... Rfd8 $1 {would have been dubious.} 20.
Qg2+ Kf8 21. Qg5 Rxd1+ 22. Rxd1 Nbd5 $1 $19) 20. Ba1 $1 Rfd8 21. Qg2+ $2 ({
White missed another chance to get back:} 21. Qe3 $1 Rxd1+ 22. Rxd1 Nbd5 23.
Qg1+ Kf8 24. exd5 Rd8 25. Qg5 Nxd5 26. Qg7+ Ke8 27. Qh8+ Qf8 28. Qe5+ $11)
21... Kf8 22. e5 (22. Qg5 Rxd1+ 23. Rxd1 Nfd7 $19) 22... Qc5+ (22... Rxd1+ 23.
Rxd1 Nfd5 24. Rg1 Qh4 $19) 23. Kb1 Nfd5 (23... Rxd1+ 24. Rxd1 Nfd5 $19) 24.
Rdg1 Nc3+ $2 {After this the fights start again.} (24... Qe3 $19) 25. Bxc3 Qxc3
26. Qg7+ Ke8 27. Qh8+ Bf8 28. Rg8 Nd7 $4 {Black commits the last mistake.} ({
The draw would have still been possible after} 28... Qb4 29. Rhg1 $1 (29. e6
Ke7) 29... Nd7 30. e6 fxe6 31. Qxh7 exf5 32. Qxf5 Nf6 33. Qxf6 Kd7 34. Rxf8
Qxf8 35. Rg7+ Kc8 36. Qe6+ Kb8 37. Qe5+ Qd6 38. Qxd6+ Rxd6 39. Rg8+ Kc7 40.
Rxa8 Rh6 $11) 29. Bxd7+ Rxd7 30. Rxf8+ Ke7 31. Rxf7+ Kxf7 32. e6+ {A nice
geometry which probably was missed by Black.} 1-0

