Yerevan 2014}) 8... Be6 9. Qc1 Nbd7 10. Bc4 Bf5 11. O-O Rc8 12. Re1 b5 13. Bf1
c5 {Wojtkiewicz,A -Shabalov,A /San Diego 2006}) 7... O-O $1 (7... Be6 8. Qd3
Nd5 {was played for the first time in the legendary Avro tournament in 1938 in
the game Euwe-Botvinnik. Nowadays it is well known to be insufficient for
equality.} 9. Nxd5 $1 (9. Bd2 Nb4 10. Qb1 c5 11. dxc5 N8a6 $11 {Euwe,
