Qb6 12. Bc3 O-O 13. Be2 Rd8 14. O-O $14 {Makogonov,V-Reshevsky,S/ Leningrad &
Moscow 1939}) 10. e3 {In this symmetrical structure with the open c-file,
which is typical for the Slav Exchange, Black's only problem seems to be the
activity of his Bg7. While Black will be busy reactivating it via f8, White
will create strong pressure on the open file. In any case, the best Black can
hope for is equality.} Nc6 11. Be2 Qa5+ (11... Bf5 12. Qd2 O-O 13. O-O $14) 12.
Qd2 Rc8 13. O-O Bg4 {Here I propose an interesting novelty} (13... Qxd2 14.
Nxd2 O-O 15. Nb3 $14) 14. b4 $1 $146 ({improving on} 14. Qd3 O-O 15. h3 Bf5 16.
Qb3 Qb4 $11 {Kovalenko,I -Mamedyarov, S /Riga 2013}) 14... Qxb4 (14... Nxb4 15.
Rfb1 Rc2 16. Qxb4 {This queen sacrifice is the main point behind my novelty.}
Rc1+ 17. Rxc1 Qxb4 18. Rab1 Qa5 19. Ne5 $16) 15. Qxb4 Nxb4 16. Rab1 Nxa2 17.
Rxb7 $14) 8. e4 $1 {Now we enter deep Gruenfeld theory: 1.d4 Nf6 2.c4 g6 3.Nc3
