Bxe2 16. Nxg6 $1 hxg6 17. Kxe2 $14) 11. Qc2 Nbd7 12. Be2 Nb6 13. Ng5 Bg4 14. f3
Bd7 15. Nc5 $18) (8... a5 {Black achieved nothing in Shishkin, V -Lupulescu, C
Bucarest 2007} 9. Be2 b5 10. Qd3 Ba6 11. Qc2 Nbd7 12. O-O Qb6 13. Rad1 $14 {
White comfortably completed development and enjoyed a huge space advantage.}) (
8... Na6 9. Be2 Qa5 10. Bd2 $1 $14 ({Be aware of the famous trick} 10. O-O $6
Nxe4 11. Nxe4 Qf5 $11 {[%csl Re4,Rf4] Flear -Topalov Mesa open 1992})) 9. Qb3
$1 ({After} 9. Qd3 {Black has many good continuations like Ba6, Qa5 or b4, but
