9... Na6 10. c5 $1 Bf5 11. Qd1 Nb4 12. O-O {, and Black's activity is only
temporary.} Bd3 (12... Nd3 $2 13. Nb3 Qa6 14. Rb1 $1 $18) 13. a3 $16) (8...
Nbd7 9. Be2 Re8 {preparing e5 is too slow, White keeps a small advantage after}
10. O-O e5 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. Bxe5 Rxe5 13. cxd5 cxd5 14. Nf3 Re8 15. Rfd1 $14)
(8... Na6 $5 9. Be2 $1 (9. a3 {This prophylactic move is White's usual
