Qe7 (14... e5 15. Be3 Kh8 {Nguyen Duc Hoa -Ni Hua Sharjah UAE 2014} 16. Qc2 $14
) (14... Re8 15. Be3 Qe7 16. f4 $5 f6 (16... f5 $5 17. Bd2 $1) 17. Rf2 Kh8 {
Batchimeg,T -Guseva,M Khanty-Mansiysk RUS 2014} 18. e5 $5 $14) 15. Be3 Rfd8 {
Black has the simple plan to improve the position with f6 and Bf7, getting the
bishop back into play and at the same time preparing the break e6-e5.} 16. f4
Kh8 17. Rf2 f6 (17... f5 {is more active, but it creates unnecessary problems
on the dark squares.} 18. Bd2 $1 Nb6 19. Bxb4 axb4 20. Qc5 Qxc5 21. Nxc5 fxe4
22. Bxe4 Rxd4 23. Bg2 Ra7 24. Re1 $36) 18. Bd2 $5 e5 19. Bxb4 axb4 20. fxe5
fxe5 21. d5 Rac8 $6 {Black missed a very strong idea in Ivanchuk,V - Vallejo
Pons,F Istanbul 2012.} ({The immediate} 21... cxd5 22. exd5 Rac8 {is much
better:} 23. Qh4 Qxh4 24. gxh4 Nf6 25. Re1 b6 26. a5 bxa5 27. Nxa5 e4 28. Nc6
Rd6 29. Nxb4 Rb6 $44) ({or} 21... Bf7 $5 22. Rd2 Bg8 23. a5 Rac8 24. Qe2 Nf6
$11) 22. Rc1 $1 Nb6 23. Qc5 $1 Qxc5 24. Nxc5 cxd5 25. Bh3 $1 {Playing 21...
Rac8, Black probably missed this intermediate move.} Ra8 26. a5 $1 {, and
