mainline, I would like to turn your attention to the other rarely played but
nevertheless solid options: 8...Nb6 and 8...Bd6.} Nb6 9. Qb3 Qd5 {Black's idea
is simple - in the endgame White's space advantage will be less important.} 10.
Nbd2 (10. Qd1 {avoiding queen exchange, but at the price of a pawn. The
sacrifice is correct, but it is not to everybody's taste to give away material
without concrete aim.} Bxb1 11. Rxb1 Qxa2 12. Bg5 (12. Bd2 Qd5 13. Re1 Be7 14.
e4 Qd8 15. Ba5 $44) 12... Be7 13. Ne5 O-O 14. Qd3 Qa4 15. Rfc1 Qb4 {, and here
