20. Rxd1 Qc6 21. Be5 $14) 19... Be7 20. Be3 Bd3 $132) (11... Rfe8) 12. Nc3 Ne4
13. Ne1 (13. Nh4 $5 $146 {is an interesting option, which is still untested.}
Bxh4 (13... Nxc3 14. bxc3 Bxh4 15. gxh4 e5 16. e4 Be6 17. Bg5 f6 18. Be3 $16)
14. Nxe4 Be7 15. Nc3 Nf6 $1 {, and White has difficulties with e3-e4, as the
pawn d4 is hanging. In case of the immediate} 16. e4 Bg4 17. f3 e5 18. Na4 Qb4
