included this game among the ten theoretically most important is that I wanted
to show you the best way to meet the rare line 4... Bg4.} d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. c4
c6 4. Qc2 Bg4 5. Ne5 $1 Bh5 {Black has not much of a choice.} ({Giving the
bishop pair for nothing is not a clever idea.} 5... e6 6. Nxg4 Nxg4 7. e3 Nd7
8. h3 Ngf6 9. Nc3 $14) 6. cxd5 $1 cxd5 (6... Qxd5 7. e3 e6 8. Nc3 Qd8 9. f3 $14
) (6... Nxd5 7. Qb3 Nd7 (7... Qb6 $4 8. Qh3 $18 {is a well-known opening trick.
}) 8. Qxb7 Nxe5 9. dxe5 Rc8 10. e6 $16) 7. Nc3 e6 8. e4 $1 {The only idea to
challenge Black's opening experiment.} a6 {Defending against Bb5.} (8... dxe4
9. Bb5+ $18) 9. Qb3 (9. Qa4+ Nbd7 10. Nxd7 Nxd7 11. exd5 exd5 12. Bd3 Bd6 13.
O-O O-O 14. Nxd5 Nb6 15. Nxb6 Qxb6 16. Be3 f5 $132) 9... b5 $6 {A bad move,
but Black is short of good advice anyway.} (9... Nc6 10. Nxc6 bxc6 11. Qb7 c5
12. Be3 Be7 13. Qc6+ Nd7 14. exd5 Rc8 15. Qxa6 cxd4 16. Bxd4 e5 17. Be3 Bb4 18.
Qa4) (9... Nbd7 10. Bg5 $40) (9... dxe4 $6 10. Qxb7 $18) 10. exd5 Nxd5 (10...
exd5 11. Bg5) 11. g4 Bg6 12. Bg2 Bb4 13. O-O Bxc3 14. bxc3 O-O 15. f4 $1 {
Black is completely lost.} Nb6 16. Bxa8 Nxa8 17. f5 exf5 18. Ba3 $18 (18. Nxg6
hxg6 19. gxf5) *

