1. d4 {In this game White sacrificed a whole rook and got more than sufficient
compensation. But then he made a couple of mistakes and in the end failed to
win a rook down, in a study-like position.} d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Qc2 g6 5.
Bf4 Bg7 6. e3 O-O 7. Nc3 Na6 8. a3 $1 Bf5 9. Qb3 Qb6 {Black offer the queen
exchange having in mind to avoid the miserable structure thanks to the
intermediate move Nb4. But it is met with a very strong refutation.} 10. Qxb6
axb6 11. cxd5 Nb4 12. dxc6 $3 {Great novelty !} Nc2+ 13. Kd1 Nxa1 14. cxb7 Rad8
(14... Rab8 15. Ba6 $1) 15. Bc4 $1 {covering b3 and preparing Ke2} Nd7 $6 ({
Black can't solve the problems, but the relatively best defence was} 15... Ne4
16. Ke2 $1 {is simplest,} ({although the only move played is} 16. Nxe4 Bxe4 17.
b8=Q Rxb8 18. Bxb8 Rxb8 19. Ng5 {Svetushkin - Al Marandi 2013 and Caron -Pinol
2004 proved that White should win.}) 16... Nc2 (16... Nxc3+ 17. bxc3 Nc2 18. a4
Be4 19. b8=Q Rxb8 20. Bxb8 Rxb8 21. Bd3) 17. Nd5 Rd7 18. b8=Q Rxb8 19. Bxb8 Be6
20. Rc1 Nxd4+ 21. exd4 Bxd5 22. Bxd5 Rxd5 23. Rc8+ Bf8 24. Ke3 Nf6 25. Bf4 Kg7
26. Be5 $18) 16. Ke2 (16. Bc7 $1 $18) 16... Nc2 (16... e5 17. Nxe5 Nxe5 (17...
Bxe5 18. dxe5 Nc2) 18. dxe5 b5 19. Nxb5 Nb3 20. Nd6 $18) 17. Rc1 (17. Nd5)
17... e5 18. Nxe5 Bxe5 19. dxe5 Nc5 20. Nd5 Kg7 {Black missed the last chance.}
(20... Nd3 $1 21. Bxd3 Bxd3+ 22. Kxd3 Rxd5+ 23. Kxc2 Rc5+ 24. Kb1 Rxc1+ 25.
Kxc1 Rb8 26. a4 Rxb7 27. Kc2 $18) 21. Bg5 Rd7 22. Bf6+ $18 Kh6 23. f3 $2 (23.
Be7 Rb8 24. Bd6 Rbxb7 25. Bf8+ Kh5 26. f3 $18) 23... Be6 (23... b5 24. Ba2 Bd3+
25. Kf2 Be4 $1 $13) 24. Rxc2 Bxd5 {Black is a rook up. The position is like a
study, but with multiple solutions.} 25. Bb5 $2 (25. Bxd5 Rxd5 26. Rc4 g5 27.
h4 Kg6 28. hxg5 h5 (28... h6 29. b4 Nxb7 30. gxh6 Kxh6 31. Rh4+ Kg6 32. Rg4+
Kh7 33. e4 Rd7 34. f4) 29. b4 (29. gxh6) 29... Nxb7 30. f4 Rd7 (30... Kf5 31.
e4+) 31. Rc1 Kf5 32. Kf3 Ke6 33. e4 Rd3+ 34. Ke2 Rd4 35. Ke3 {Domination plus
mating ideas.}) 25... Rxb7 26. g4 $2 (26. Rd2 Be6 27. Rd4 g5 28. h4 $44) 26...
Ne6 $6 (26... Bb3 $19) (26... Rc7) 27. h4 (27. Rd2 $1 Nc7 28. Kf2 g5 29. Be2
$132) 27... Rc7 28. Rxc7 Nxc7 29. Bd3 Ne6 30. Kf2 Rc8 31. g5+ $2 (31. f4 $5 Nc5
32. Be2 Ne4+ 33. Kg1 Rc1+ 34. Kh2 Rh1+ 35. Kxh1 Ng3+ 36. Kg1 Nxe2+ 37. Kf2 Nc1
38. Bd8 b5 $17) 31... Kh5 32. Kg3 Rc1 33. Be2 Bc4 34. Bxc4 Rxc4 35. f4 Rc2 0-1

