1. Nf3 d5 2. d4 Nf6 3. c4 c6 4. Qc2 dxc4 5. Qxc4 Bg4 6. Nbd2 Nbd7 7. g3 e6 8.
Bg2 Be7 9. O-O O-O 10. b3 {Following the most natural path. The other moves are
} (10. Ne5) (10. Qb3) 10... Qa5 (10... a5 $5) 11. h3 Bf5 ({After this game,
everybody played only} 11... Bh5 $1) 12. Nh4 $1 {White's main aim in this line
is to exchange or isolate that bishop.} Nb6 {White queen is trapped} ({White
can use the same idea after} 12... b5 13. Qxc6 Rac8 14. Nxf5 $1 $16) 13. Nxf5
$3 Nxc4 ({Wiser was} 13... Qxf5 14. Qc3 Nbd5 15. Qb2 $14 {White won the bishop
pair and is going to occupy the centre with e4.}) 14. Nxe7+ Kh8 15. Nxc4 {
If White manages to save his knight from e7, he will have more than sufficient
compensation for the queen.} Qc7 (15... Qa6 16. a4 Rfe8 17. Ba3 Nd5 18. Nxd5
exd5 19. Nd6 Rxe2 20. Nxf7+ Kg8 21. Ne5 $16) 16. Ba3 Rae8 (16... Rfe8 17. Bd6
Qd8 18. Nxc6 bxc6 19. Bxc6 h6 20. Bxe8 Qxe8 21. f3 {will be very similar to
the game.}) 17. Nxc6 $1 {The winning idea - White gains a rook and bishop for
the queen, and Black's pawn on c6 will be weak.} bxc6 18. Bxf8 ({Playing for
domination was interesting:} 18. Rfc1 Rg8 19. Ne5 Nd5 20. Rxc6 Qb7 21. Rac1 $16
) 18... Rxf8 19. Rfc1 $16 {The c6 pawn is doomed.} Nd7 20. b4 $1 g6 ({The best
chance was} 20... e5 21. Na5 exd4 22. Nxc6 d3 23. exd3 f5 24. d4 f4 25. Rc3
fxg3 26. fxg3 Re8 $16) 21. a3 (21. Na5 Qd6 22. Nxc6 Nb8 23. b5 Nxc6 24. bxc6
Qxd4 25. e3 Qe5 26. Rab1 $16) 21... e5 22. dxe5 Nxe5 23. Na5 Qe7 24. Ra2 $1 g5
(24... h5 25. Rac2 h4 26. g4 Rd8 27. Nxc6 Nxc6 28. Bxc6 Kg7 29. Bf3) 25. Rac2
Rd8 26. Nxc6 Nxc6 27. Bxc6 $16 {/+-} Kg7 28. Bf3 Qe6 29. Rc5 $1 {White is
technically winning.} h6 30. Kg2 Rd6 31. Ra5 (31. Rc6) 31... Ra6 32. Rcc5 Rxa5
33. Rxa5 Qb6 34. Be4 Qd4 35. Bd3 $1 Qb6 36. Kg1 Qd4 37. Kg2 f6 38. Rb5 h5 39.
a4 h4 40. g4 Kf8 41. a5 Ke7 42. a6 $18 Kd6 43. Rb8 Qd5+ 44. Kg1 Qc6 45. b5 Qc7
46. Rb7 Qc1+ 47. Kg2 Qc5 48. Be4 f5 49. Bxf5 Qd5+ 50. e4 Qc5 51. b6 axb6 52.
Rd7+ Kc6 53. a7 Qa5 54. e5 Qa4 55. e6 Kc5 56. e7 Qc6+ 57. Kg1 Qa8 58. Bg6 1-0

